'''Aurèle Florian Amenda''' (born 31 July 2003) is a Swiss professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{German football updater|EinFrank}} club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|637254}}</ref>

==Club career==
Amenda signed his first professional contract in December 2021 with [[BSC Young Boys]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bscyb.ch/news?nID=12827|title=Aurèle Amenda Erhält Profivertrag|trans-title=Aurèle Amenda Signs Professional Contract|date=21 December 2021|accessdate=2 May 2022|website=bscyb.ch|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bernerzeitung.ch/profivertrag-fuer-yb-talent-194115114357|title=Profivertrag für YB-Talent|trans-title=Professional contract for YB talent|date=21 December 2021|accessdate=2 May 2022|website=bernerzeitung.ch|language=German}}</ref> He made his professional debut for the club on 13 February 2022, replacing [[Wilfried Kanga]] in the 85th minute with a 3–1 league win over [[FC Basel|Basel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/02/13/switzerland/super-league/bsc-young-boys-bern/fc-basel/3524279/|title=BSC Young Boys - FC Basel|date=13 February 2022|accessdate=12 January 2023|website=Soccerway}}</ref> He made three more appearances in the 2021–22 season, on 3 April 2022 against Basel,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-qa/match/basel-v-young-boys/lineups/8mbzygto3b6s8ykb3r2oa5y50|title=Basel v Young Boys|date=3 April 2022|accessdate=12 January 2023|website=goal.com}}</ref> on 9 April 2022 against [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/swiss-super-league/2021-2022/live-bsc-young-boys-fc-lausanne-sport_mtc1277281/live-lineup.shtml|title=BSC YOUNG BOYS - FC LAUSANNE-SPORT|date=9 April 2022|accessdate=12 January 2023|website=eurosport.com}}</ref> and on 22 May 2022 against [[Grasshopper Club Zürich|Grasshoppers]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sofascore.com/grasshopper-club-zurich-young-boys/VYsZY|title=Young Boys - Grasshopper Club Zürich|date=22 May 2022|website=sofascore.com}}</ref> finishing the season with four games in total.
 
At the start of the 2022–23 season, Amenda made his European debut on 28 July 2022 with Young Boys in a 3–0 win against [[FK Liepāja|Liepāja]] in the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] qualifier match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/match/2035138--young-boys-vs-liepaja/|title=Young Boys-Liepaja|date=28 July 2022|website=[[UEFA]]}}</ref> He played two matches for Young Boys in the [[2022–23 Swiss Super League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bscyb.ch/kader?s=365|title=Aurele Amenda|accessdate=12 January 2023|website=Bscyb.ch}}</ref>

On 7 February 2024, Amenda was announced at [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] from 1 July 2024, signing a five year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/aurele-amenda-wird-adlertraeger-156606|title=Aurèle Amenda to become an Eagle|website=en.eintracht.de}}</ref>

==International career==
Amenda represented Switzerland at youth international level.<ref name=wf/>

Amenda made his [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]] debut on 15 November 2024 in a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|Nations League]] game against Serbia at [[Letzigrund]]. He played the full game in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/699002|title=Switzerland v Serbia game report|date=15 November 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Amenda is a centre-back with physical attributes including height and speed. He participates in a defensive play through his aerial and ground challenges, including tackling. In addition to these attributes, he moves the ball forward by dribbling into the opposition's half or using long-range passing. He is noted for maintaining composure in various situations and demonstrates having leadership qualities.<ref name=bolzplazz>{{cite web|url=https://www.bolzplazz.com//post/swiss-talent-watch-aur%C3%A8le-amenda-das-neuste-yb-juwel|title=Swiss Talent Watch: Aurèle Amenda – das neuste YB-Juwel|trans-title=Swiss Talent Watch: Aurèle Amenda - the latest YB jewel|first=Emmanuel|last=Staub|date=9 January 2022|accessdate=29 December 2022|website=bolzplazz.com|language=German}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Aurèle Amenda was born and raised in Switzerland. He is the child of a family originally from Cameroon.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=kmedia-ch.ch|url=https://www.kmedia-ch.ch/post/aur%C3%A8le-amenda-je-veux-devenir-un-titulaire-%C3%A0-part-enti%C3%A8re-%C3%A0-yb/|title=Aurèle Amenda : "Je veux devenir un titulaire à part entière à YB !"|date=1 June 2022 |accessdate=12 January 2023}}</ref>

